      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yeah, I want SkImageFilter::CropRect (no \"s\") to go away entirely. Its concept of edge flags aren\u0027t used anywhere any more so essentially a wrapper around an optional SkRect. Unfortunately, every image filter has to take a CropRect and use it in the correct way.\n\nI want to have an SkCropImageFilter that handles all of this logic. Users can manually wrap filters or compose filters with a crop (to control input and output cropping separately). The crop filter will also control tile modes at the crop edges (moving tile mode out of blur/matrix convolution). At this point, these factory functions in SkImageFilters would still exist, but would simply automatically wrap the main filter with whatever crop filter was requested.",
